This paper focuses on style separation and synthesis in object photographs, which is a problem commonly studied in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) communities. The proposed method involves the use of a generative adversarial network (GAN), which is a popular deep learning technique for image generation and manipulation, and is often studied in the context of computer vision and machine learning. Additionally, the paper involves the use of an encoder network, which is a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for learning representations of data. The paper also involves experiments on image datasets, which is a common topic in multimedia (cs.MM) and graphics (cs.GR) communities.
